The exxonu is now pushed on through
the central door. It was a small stage,
but large enough to allow of Ajax being
shon surrounded by some of the slaugh-
tered animals. The word royn in 347,
and the language of vv. 351 ff., show that
the carnage was represented. The other
plays in which Sophocles has used the
eccyclema are the Antigone (1294, where
see n.), and the Electra (1464 fi., n.).
